FedEx Corp (XNYS: FDX) announced plans to separate its less-then-truckload (LT) freight division, FedEx Freight (XNYS: FDXF). The distribution is expected to occur by June 2026. SPDJI will treat this transaction as a zero price spin off.

Union Pacific Corp (XNYS: UNP) is to acquire Norfolk Southern Corp (XNYS: NSC) for cash and stock. Shareholders will receive $88.82 USD cash and 1.00 UNP share for every NSC share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close by early 2027.

Kimberly-Clark (XNAS: KMB) is to acquire Kenvue Inc (XNYS: KVUE) for cash and stock. Shareholders will receive $3.50 USD cash and 0.14625 KMB shares for every KVUE share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in the second half of 2026
Thoma Bravo is to acquire Dayforce Inc (XNYSE: DAY) for $70.00 USD cash per share. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in early 2026.

Charter Communications Inc (XNAS: CHTR)  is to acquire Liberty Broadband Corp A/C (XNAS: LBRDA/ LBDRK). Shareholders will receive 0.236 CHTR shares for every LBRDA/ LBDRK held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close on June 30, 2027.

American Water Works Co (XNYS: AWK) is to acquire Essential Utilities Inc (XNYS: WTRG) for stock. Shareholders will receive 0.305 AWK shares for every WTRG share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close by the end of first quarter of 2027.

BX and TPG and others are to acquire Hologic Inc. (XNAS: HOLX) for $76.00 USD cash per share plus a non-tradeable CVR worth up to $3.00 USD. The transaction is expected to close in H1 2026, pending shareholder approval, regulatory approvals, and other customary closing conditions.

Palo Alto Networks (XNAS: PANW) is to acquire Cyber-Ark Software Ltd (XNAS: CYBR) for cash and stock. Shareholders will receive $45.00 USD cash and 2.2005 PANW shares for every CYBR share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close during the second half of PANW's fiscal 2026 (which ends on July 31, 2026)

VICI Properties Inc. (XNYS: VICI) and Blake Sartini are to acquire Golden Entertainment Inc. (XNAS:GDEN) for stock and cash. GDEN Shareholders will receive 0.902 shares of VICI and $2.75 USD cash for every share of GDEN held. The transaction is expected to close in the second half of 2026, pending shareholder approval, regulatory approvals and other customary closing conditions.

Boeing Co(XNYS:BA) will acquire Spirit Aerosystems Holdings A(XNYS:SPR) in an all-stock transaction. SPR SHs will receive 0.25 shares of BA common stock for each of their shares of SPR common stock if the Closing Price is at or below $149.00, and 0.18 shares of BA common stock for each of their shares of SPR common stock if the Closing Price is at or above $206.94. The transaction is expected to close mid-2025, subject to regulatory and Spirit shareholder approvals.

Huntington Bancshares Inc (XNAS: HBAN) is to acquire Cadence Bank (XNAS: CADE) for stock. Shareholders will receive 2.475 HBAN shares for every CADE share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in the first quarter of 2026.

Mars Inc. is to acquire Kellanova Co (XNYS: K) for $83.50 USD cash per share. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in the first half of 2025.

Fifth Third Bancorp (XNAS: FITB) is to acquire Comerica Inc (XNYS: CMA) for stock. Shareholders will receive 1.8663 FITB shares for every MA share held. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in the first quarter of 2026.

An investor consortium comprised of PIF, Silver Lake, and Affinity Partners are to acquire Electronic Arts (XNAS: EA) for $210.00 USD cash per share. The transaction, which is subject to shareholder and regulatory approvals, is expected to close in the first quarter of 2027.

Skyworks Solutions Inc (XNAS: SWKS) is to acquire Qorvo Inc (XNAS: QRVO) for cash and stock. QRVO shareholders will receive $32.50 USD cash and 0.960 shares of SWKS for every share of QRVO held. The transaction is expected to close in early calendar year 2027, pending shareholder approval, regulatory approvals and other customary closing conditions.
